<br>
1)  I'ld like to find an in-game mentor for my character; I play a High Elf Magician, who calls himself a Pyromancer.  Anything from a master-apprentice relationship to just a wizened village elder would be wonderful.  I'ld like someone to develop my roleplaying skill against.  The experienced players I've seen tend to be running about at full enhanced speed everywhere they go.  If such noble beings are in such a rush, my lowly character feels out of place to approach them.  Likewise, typically when they aren't running around they are surrounded by a whole host of others and are busy casting spells.  My character has no desire to interrupt their preperations.....<br>
<br>
2)  Similarly I'ld like advice on finding low-level roleplayers to adventure with.  I want to advance, but I don't care if its not as fast as &quot;optimal&quot;.  I've found three groups over the past three nights with overlapping members.  All tolerate roleplay, but none join in, so I find myself stopping as well.  Sadly they are very aggressive about joining fights that others are involved in.  I don't know if its out of ignorance about kill steals, a desire to help the besieged or what.  In two cases when I told them that it looked like the other people had it under control, they backed off before it caused problems.  The third time I was still running to the scene when I noticed what was happening and then it was too late.  The victim complained to me, as I was about to tell the group off.  I apoligized to the victim, left the group immediately, and proceeded to have a nice in-game discussion with the victim, which has already given my character more to think about.  I definately won't be grouping with them again, without a discussion about &quot;sharing.&quot;  Any suggestions for finding more suitable companions.<br>
<br>
3)  Similarly, is it ever right to jump in an assist someone?  When I've seen an a fellow newbie surrounded by a swarm of wasps and can see their health dropping fast, I'ld like to help.  I've always sent a tell asking if they want help, non have every responded, all have died in another minute or so.  While my character is good and would want to help another elf, I don't want the bad will of players.  Similarly if someone is running from the orc camp with a pack of 4-5 orcs following, should I try to distract some/all of the orcs?  I'm a magician, I don't have any beneficial spells I can cast on others yet so I can't help without joining the battle directly....<br>
<br>
4)  Roleplay advice---last night there was a powerful dark elf sitting near in in Felewithe before the bridge.  His tag was green, I don't know what that means, was guessing maybe its a GM/Guide?  In either case it looked like a wonderful roleplay situation, but I (the player) was too afraid to do anything.  I tried finding other PCs but the zone was rather empty and I couldn't get back out to the Feydark without passing him, the character was definately too afraid to try to run by... shouting would only draw attention to me.  If I confronted him, likely denouncing him, I would probably get challenged to a duel... I'ld have to accept, but whats the point he could probably kill me with a single blow....  Suggestions for how to handle this in the future?<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.<br>
