<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1) The in game mentor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Well, sure high-level players are often busy, but they are as often bored. Just try to approach them with nice roleplaying and I am sure you will not have to seek for long.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2) The stopping roleplaying when you join a group</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Just continue your roleplaying, no matter what the others do. You will draw them in, and if not, you can still leave. There are a lot of nice players on FV. Of course you often have to cut down roleplaying slightly when in groups, in order to function effectively, but by no means it has to stop completely. (Maybe in an excellent group you need not cut down at all ?)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3) Helping others</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
