OK, now... bind wounds. You don't have to bind others. Running around finding injured folk is the least efficient way to get skill. Target yourself. Nuke yourself under half, bind. Lather, rinse, repeat... until you max your skill each level. You can also jump off a cliff, but be careful that you don't jump off anything high enough to kill you. Falling damage is variable, nukes are a bit more of a known quantity. Either way, doing this will assure you that you always are at optimum skill in binding.<br>
<br>
Mages are pretty awful at any type of hunting that requires decent crowd control... we don't have any. So don't look to everything-jumps-you-at-once-camps for your primary experience, unless you are grouped or everything is low blue. If you are talking about orc camps in Faydark and a new damage shield, I am guessing you are around level 7-8ish? Get out of Faydark!<br>
